<% content_for :title, "Field Guide" %>
<div class="ps-root ps-tut-root">
  <%= render "studies/topbar", study_name: "The Field Guide", panes: 4, sync: false, saved: true %>

  <div class="ps-tut">
    <header class="ps-tut-hero">
      <div class="eyebrow">&#9769; &nbsp; A Field Guide To Your Desk &nbsp; &#9769;</div>
      <h1>Everything you can do here</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Parallel Scripture is a quiet desk for the Word — lay passages side by side, trace
        cross-references, study the original words, and let a careful AI help you see the text in
        context. Here is the whole desk, tool by tool.
      </p>
      <div class="ps-tut-hero-cta">
        <% tour_target = @resume ? study_path(@resume, tour: 1) : root_path %>
        <%= link_to "&#9737; &nbsp; Take the interactive tour".html_safe, tour_target, class: "cta" %>
        <%= link_to "Back to your desk", root_path, class: "cta secondary", style: "text-decoration:none;" %>
      </div>
    </header>

    <%# 1 — Parallel panes %>
    <section class="ps-tut-section">
      <div class="ps-tut-copy">
        <div class="ps-tut-kicker">I</div>
        <h2>Up to four passages, side by side</h2>
        <p>Compare the same verse across translations — KJV, ASV, BSB, WEB and more — or set different
           verses next to each other. Use the <span class="kbd">1</span>–<span class="kbd">4</span>
           selector in the topbar to choose how many panes are open.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ps-tut-art">
        <div class="ps-tut-panes">
          <% [["John III", "KJV"], ["John III", "BSB"]].each do |ref, tr| %>
            <div class="ps-tut-pane">
              <div class="ps-tut-pane-head"><span class="num">&#8544;</span> <span class="ref"><%= ref %></span> <span class="tr"><%= tr %></span></div>
              <div class="ps-tut-pane-body"><span class="v">16</span> For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son…</div>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <%# 2 — Reference lookup %>
    <section class="ps-tut-section reverse">
      <div class="ps-tut-copy">
        <div class="ps-tut-kicker">II</div>
        <h2>Type a reference the way you say it</h2>
        <p>The parser understands the natural forms — no rigid syntax to learn.</p>
        <div class="ps-tut-chips">
          <% %w[Jn\ 3:16 Rom\ 5 1\ Cor\ 13 Ps\ 23 romans\ 5:1-11].each do |r| %>
            <span class="ps-tut-chip"><%= r %></span>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ps-tut-art">
        <div class="ps-tut-field">
          <span class="cur">John 3:16&#8203;<span class="caret"></span></span>
          <span class="go">go &#8629;</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <%# 3 — Cross references %>
    <section class="ps-tut-section">
      <div class="ps-tut-copy">
        <div class="ps-tut-kicker">III</div>
        <h2>Cross-references, one click away</h2>
        <p>Click any <strong>verse number</strong> to open the Treasury of Scripture Knowledge drawer,
           sorted by weight. Load any reference straight into a pane.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ps-tut-art">
        <div class="ps-tut-drawer">
          <div class="ps-tut-drawer-head">&#167; &nbsp; Cross References &middot; John 3:16</div>
          <% [["Romans 5:8", 58], ["1 John 4:9", 47], ["John 3:36", 33]].each do |ref, votes| %>
            <div class="ps-tut-xref"><span class="r"><%= ref %></span><span class="dots"><%= "●" * [votes/18, 1].max %></span></div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <%# 4 — AI Rabbi (featured) %>
    <section class="ps-tut-section reverse ps-tut-feature">
      <div class="ps-tut-copy">
        <div class="ps-tut-kicker">&#10018;</div>
        <h2>Ask the AI Rabbi</h2>
        <p>Highlight a phrase and choose <strong>✢ Rabbi</strong>. It reads the
           <em>whole chapter</em> and the verse's cross-references before answering, and stays under
           strict rules of sound interpretation: context first, Scripture interprets Scripture,
           never beyond what is written. It cites references — the verse wording always comes from
           our own translations, never the model.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ps-tut-art">
        <div class="ps-tut-rabbi">
          <div class="sel">&ldquo;God so loved the world&rdquo;</div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="lbl">Summary</div>
            <p>God's love is the ground and motive of the gospel — the gift of the Son flows from it.</p>
            <div class="lbl">A caution</div>
            <p class="caution">&ldquo;World&rdquo; here speaks of its scope and wickedness, not of universal salvation.</p>
            <div class="refs"><span>Romans 5:8</span><span>1 John 4:9</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <%# 5 — AI Find a verse %>
    <section class="ps-tut-section">
      <div class="ps-tut-copy">
        <div class="ps-tut-kicker">IV</div>
        <h2>Find a verse from a thought</h2>
        <p>Describe a half-remembered idea and the assistant returns matching passages, every one
           validated against our text. The <span class="kbd">&#10038; Find</span> button opens it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ps-tut-art">
        <div class="ps-tut-find">
          <div class="q">&ldquo;where Paul says we're saved by grace, not works&rdquo;</div>
          <div class="results"><span>Ephesians 2:8-9</span><span>Romans 3:28</span><span>Titus 3:5</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <%# 6 — Original-language study %>
    <section class="ps-tut-section reverse">
      <div class="ps-tut-copy">
        <div class="ps-tut-kicker">V</div>
        <h2>Study the original words</h2>
        <p>In the King James text, tap any word for its Strong's number, transliteration, definition
           and every occurrence. Turn on <em>Lemma (Strong's)</em> in the View menu to see the
           transliteration beneath each tagged word, and <em>Word diff</em> to highlight where two
           translations differ.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ps-tut-art">
        <div class="ps-tut-lex">
          <div class="word">loved <span class="g">&#945;&#947;&#945;&#960;&#940;&#969; &middot; G25</span></div>
          <div class="def">agapaō — to love, to welcome, to be fond of; of God's redeeming love.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <%# 7 — More tools grid %>
    <section class="ps-tut-more">
      <h2 class="ps-tut-more-title">And at hand whenever you need them</h2>
      <div class="ps-tut-more-grid">
        <% [
             ["&#128220;", "Commentary", "Matthew Henry's exposition, opened beside the text from the 📜 in each pane."],
             ["&#9998;", "Highlights & notes", "Four colours, with a study note attached to each highlight; ✎ marks the ones with notes."],
             ["&#9906;", "Full-Bible search", "Find any phrase across the whole text and jump straight to it."],
             ["&#9658;", "Read aloud", "Have a passage read by the browser — no network, no cost."],
             ["&#9680;", "Memorize mode", "Blank the words, then tap to reveal — for scripture-memory drills."],
             ["&#128272;", "Preach mode", "Project verse-by-verse, fused 1–3 per slide, with large auto-fit text. ⧉ Project opens a second-screen output window that follows your console."],
             ["&#9737;", "Go Live", "The congregation scans a QR and the Scripture follows the pulpit on their phones — live, no account needed."],
             ["&#10070;", "Reading plans", "Pace a book, the NT, the year, or your own path — and tick each day done."],
             ["&#9776;", "Reading view", "Text size, candle/day theme, sync-scroll — all in the View menu."]
           ].each do |icon, title, desc| %>
          <div class="ps-tut-more-card">
            <span class="orn"><%= icon.html_safe %></span>
            <span class="t"><%= title %></span>
            <span class="d"><%= desc %></span>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="ps-tut-foot">
      <div class="rule-orn"><span class="line"></span><span>&#10086;</span><span class="line"></span></div>
      <% tour_target = @resume ? study_path(@resume, tour: 1) : root_path %>
      <%= link_to "&#9737; &nbsp; Take the interactive tour".html_safe, tour_target, class: "cta" %>
      <%= link_to "Begin at your desk", root_path, class: "cta secondary", style: "text-decoration:none;" %>
    </footer>
  </div>
</div>
